            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <p>
              Suppose we want to draw the triangle with vertices <m>A=(2,3)</m>, <m>B=(-3,1)</m>, and <m>C=(4,-2)</m>. As a shorthand notation, we will denote the vector from the point <m>A</m> to the point <m>B</m> as <m>\overrightarrow{AB}</m>
              <ol label="i.">
                <li>
                  <p> 
                  Determine the vectors <m>\overrightarrow{AB}</m>, <m>\overrightarrow{BC}</m>, and <m>\overrightarrow{AC}</m>.
                  </p>
