  <subsection>
    <title>The Magnitude of a Vector</title>
    <p>
      By definition, vectors have both direction and magnitude (or length). We now investigate how to calculate the magnitude of a vector. Since a vector <m>\vv</m> can be represented
      by a directed line segment, we can use the distance formula to calculate the length of the segment. This length is the <em>magnitude</em> of the vector <m>\vv</m> and is denoted <m>|\vv|</m>.
    </p>

